These technique points can be used on the marksman and tree.Characters with magical specialization gain points in wild card equal to their highest tier of magic technique and cantrips.Make two attacks, one of which must be a firearm attack.You can reload your gun as an instant action by taking 1 true damage.Whenever you take at least 3 damage, the next time you deal damage back to an enemy you heal 3 hp.You can parry with a gun. Your parry attacks have a +2 bonus. When you successfully parry, you also deal the guns damage and the enemy's turn immediately ends.By spending a swift action, you can examine a creature, living or not, and tell how much hp remaining it has.When you are defeated, you can instead feign injury. To all others it looks like you have been defeated, but you do not gain the defeated condition until the end of your next turn. During your next turn you are knocked down, but you can make a single firearm attack. If you are healed before you make the attack, this ability is immediately recharged.Spend 1 mana to augment a firearm attack to also inflict d6 bleed on hit. If you have no mana, you can instead take 1 true damage to inflict this bleed.You get a +4 bonus on survival checks to track creature you (or your allies participating in combat against them with you) have injured within the last week. This bonus increases to +8 if you or your allies inflicted bleed damage on them.You get a +2 bonus to initiative. Your first attack each combat has advantage. If you are surprised, or if ANY other creature takes damage before you can attack, you lose the advantage on first attack.

A Fiend Shifter is someone who has stolen the secrets to the powers of fiends, slowly letting this power overtake them. They only grow into a more terrifying monster capable of combating even the most terrifying the fiendish realms have to offer with the very same power they wield.{% tabs %}
